he lateral posterior gastric neurons control the movements of the lateral teeth in crustaceans.\" [PMID: 17009928]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n relationship: overlaps UBERON:8910001 ! stomatogastric ganglion\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910014.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910014.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910014.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910014.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910014.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: lateral ventricular nerve (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"The motor axons that project into the dorsal ventricular nerve bifurcate and then project into both lateral ventricular nerves.\" [PMID: 10561445]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910015.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910015.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910015.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910015.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910015.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: pyloric nerve (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"Innervates pyloric region of the stomach.\" [PMID: 2876096]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910016.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910016.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910016.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910016.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910016.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: pyloric dilator nerve (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"Innervates muscles that dilate valves of the pylorus motor neurons involved in filtering in crustaceans. Anterior burster neurons are intrinsic oscillators that are electrically coupled with pyloric dilator neurons, causing them to fire bursts of action potentials. Together these neurons inhibit lateral pyloric and pyloric neurons, forcing them to fire in alternation with the pyloric dilator neurons.\" [PMID: 2876096, PMID: 17009928]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910000 ! stomatogastric nervous system\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910017.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910017.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910017.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910017.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910017.obo\n@@ -4,8 +4,6 @@\n synonym: \"ION (sensu Cancer borealis)\" EXACT [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n def: \"The inferior esophageal nerve (ION) is one of the four nerves that make up the stomatogastric nerve (SGN).\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910010 ! stomatogastric nerve\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910018.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910018.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910018.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910018.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910018.obo\n@@ -4,8 +4,6 @@\n synonym: \"SON (sensu Cancer borealis)\" EXACT [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n def: \"The superior esophageal nerve (SON) is one of the four nerves that make up the stomatogastric nerve (SGN).\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910010 ! stomatogastric nerve\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910019.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910019.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910019.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910019.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910019.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: esophageal nerve (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"innervates the foregut and midgut\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea\n-relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura\n+relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata\n relationship: part_of UBERON:8910010 ! stomatogastric nerve\n-\n","additions":1,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo","relativePath":"terms/UBERON_8910020.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_8910020.obo\n@@ -3,8 +3,6 @@\n name: esophageal ganglion (sensu Cancer borealis)\n def: \"Neurons with cell bodies in the esophageal ganglion turn on the gastric mill rhythm and strongly affects the pyloric rhythm.\" [DOI:10.1016/B0-12-370878-8/00177-4]\n is_a: UBERON:0035014 ! functional part of brain\n relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1909-7004\n-relationship: in