{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778977881206,"sessionID":"ses_1ccaaebfbffeIrDlqkBomV8OBO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jZwEK6hVt18ctV9MfrcbhGcx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I replaced the contradictory paired `in taxon` assertions on the newly added crab/lobster stomatogastric terms with a single `in taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata`, following the issue guidance.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This change fixes the taxon constraint problem reported in issue #3454 for the stomatogastric nervous system terms added in PR #3445.\n+\n+What I changed:\n+- Updated the affected crustacean stomatogastric child terms so they no longer carry both `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea` and `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura`.\n+- Replaced those contradictory pairs with a single `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata` assertion, matching the resolution described in the issue.\n+- Checked the edited terms back into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` and reserialized the ontology with `robot convert`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- `in taxon` is exclusory and should not be used twice on the same term unless the taxa are equivalent.\n+- The issue explicitly states that Astacidea and Brachyura are both subtaxa of Pleocyemata, so Pleocyemata is the correct common exclusive taxon for these terms.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Read the imported issue context from `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Inspected the affected terms in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `obo-grep.pl`.\n+- Edited the checked-out term stanzas via the standard `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow.\n+- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Re-queried the ontology with `obo-grep.pl` to confirm the old `NCBITaxon:6712` and `NCBITaxon:6752` `in_taxon` assertions were removed from the affected batch and replaced by `NCBITaxon:6692`.\n+\n+Checklist completed:\n+- [x] Read issue and repository guidance\n+- [x] Identified the affected terms introduced by PR #3445\n+- [x] Applied the minimal taxon-constraint correction\n+- [x] Reserialized the ontology\n+- [x] Verified the updated taxon assertions\n+- [x] Committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I replaced the contradictory paired `in taxon` assertions on the newly added crab/lobster stomatogastric terms with a single `in taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata`, following the issue guidance.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+This change fixes the taxon constraint problem reported in issue #3454 for the stomatogastric nervous system terms added in PR #3445.\n+\n+What I changed:\n+- Updated the affected crustacean stomatogastric child terms so they no longer carry both `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6712 ! Astacidea` and `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6752 ! Brachyura`.\n+- Replaced those contradictory pairs with a single `relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:6692 ! Pleocyemata` assertion, matching the resolution described in the issue.\n+- Checked the ed